<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1280593 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Flavour-598x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1280" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Flavour-598x598.jpg 598w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Flavour-100x100.jpg 100w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Flavour-200x200.jpg 200w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Flavour-487x487.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Flavour-974x974.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Flavour-240x240.jpg 240w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Flavour-480x480.jpg 480w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Flavour-600x600.jpg 600w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Flavour.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> It is finally here! Sensational African music star Flavour N’abania has released his highly anticipated album, “Flavour of Africa“. For months, fans have eagerly awaited the release of the body of work that serves as a follow-up to his last record, “Awele” as well as his joint 2019 EP with songstress Chidinma. Flavour of Africa tracklist Speaking about the new release, the multiple award-winning star said: “As a musician, I’ve transformed, evolved, and transcended within my music and social responsibilities.” Released by OneRPM and Flavour’s 2Nite Entertainment, the album is a fusion of African Rhythm, Highlife, and contemporary Jazz, in one phrase: “Afro Hip-Life”. The album also boasts of collaborations with top artists like Tekno, Phyno, Larry Gaaga, Fally Ipupa, Odumeje, among others. Production credits go to Masterkraft, Rotimi Keys, Selebobo, Spax, Stadic, Jonny Blaze, Marvio and DJ Tunez. Stream the album HERE.